title: MICROECONOMETRICS AND MATLAB: AN INTRODUCTION
description: Author: Abi Adams, Damian Clarke, Simon Quinn Edition: 1 edition Publication Date: March 7, 2016 Publisher: Oxford University Press ISBN-10: 0198754507 ISBN-13: 978-0198754503 Pages: 256 pages Format: pdf Size: 2.3M ---- This book is a practical guide for theory-based empirical analysis in economics that guides the reader through the first steps when moving between economic theory and applied research. The book provides a hands-on introduction to some of the techniques that economists use for econometric estimation and shows how to convert a selection of standard and advanced estimators into MATLAB code. --- http://dlfeb.com/book/microeconometrics-and-matlab-introduction/
